Usage instructions:
1. Change the path in the '80-local.rules' and 'trigger.sh' to the folder where the corresponding files are located on your machine.
2. Copy '80-local.rules' to /etc/udev/rules.d (you will need admin privileges).
3. Run 'app.js' using Node.js server.
4. Copy 'token.txt' to a USB flash disk.
5. Add/remove the USB disc and observe the output in 'log.txt' in the same folder.

Tested on Fedora 16 with Gnome 3.2.2.1
